vEGPU Machine License
=====================

This repository contains a patch stack and release workflow for building
vEGPU Machine from QEMU-derived source.

The source tree produced by applying this repository's patch stack to the
recorded QEMU base is a QEMU-derived distribution. The QEMU emulator as a
whole is released under the GNU General Public License, version 2.

Individual source files and bundled components may carry their own license
notices. Those file-level and component-level notices remain authoritative.
As in QEMU, files with no more specific licensing information are released
under the GNU General Public License, version 2 or, at your option, any later
version. Some QEMU areas, including hw/vfio/ material, are handled under the
GPL version 2 terms applicable to QEMU.

Firmware images, guest-driver packages, display/runtime libraries, and other
third-party components distributed with a binary release are separate works
bundled for user convenience. They carry their own copyright and license
notices. Binary releases of vEGPU Machine include generated NOTICES and
LICENSES files that identify the bundled runtime payload and include the
license texts collected for that release.

OpenResearchTools changes to QEMU-derived code, DriverKit/VFIO integration,
guest-driver packaging, and build/release integration are distributed as part
of this GPL-covered QEMU-derived source tree unless an individual file or
patch hunk states a more specific license.

QEMU is a trademark of Fabrice Bellard. This repository uses the QEMU name
only to identify the upstream QEMU project, the recorded QEMU base revision,
and QEMU-derived source/runtime components. vEGPU Machine is not endorsed by,
sponsored by, or affiliated with Fabrice Bellard or the QEMU project.
